I don't take synthetic vitamins and I don't eat inflammatory foods, no refined sugar or grains and we buy mostly organic.

There's a lot you can do but of course there's no guarantee. I'd rather take my chance with the virus than risk long term side effects from a vaccine.

snippet.textDisplay:
Forcing and coercing someone to get the vaccine against their own conscience is what is selfish. No one has that right.  It is also very selfish to surrender your mind, your thinking, to others, to the authorities, without weighing out the evidence for yourself, and then expect those who have weighed out the evidence to blindly accept what you have.

God has created each of us in His image, with our own individuality, ability to think and act, and we each have the responsibility to think for ourselves, to weigh the evidence for ourselves, to come to our own conclusions and “be fully persuaded in our own minds” (Romans 14:5), and then to act on our conclusions.

The science shows that it is the unvaccinated who have recovered from a COVID infection that are the safest in our society—they are the least likely to be reinfected, the least likely to spread it, and the least likely to have a serious future case.  The unvaccinated recovered have broad, robust, and long-lasting immunity with their naturally occurring antibodies to multiple sites of the COVID virus; these antibodies are also ultra-potent to most variants. This means, again, that the unvaccinated recovered are the least likely to be spreaders.

If Djokoovic had COVID and has recovered he is actually the safest person to be around.  It makes absolutely no sense for him to be banned from future tournaments just because he hasn’t blindly accepted what everyone else has, the vaccine mandate.  Vaccine status is irrelevant; what is relevant is actual health status.
